Vice-President Samia Suluhu will begin a six-day tour of Tanga region to inspect development projects, including the launch of a guide on investment opportunities in the sisal-growing region. Briefing reporters on Sunday, Tanga Regional Commissioner Martine Shigela said the tour begins on Monday to Saturday. The Vice-President will visit Handeni, Korogwe, Muheza, Pangani, Tanga and Mkinga districts. Shigela appealed to investors and the public to join in the tour and see how the region has prepared itself for the development in the next five years.